Text.Value: Unh. Dissatisfying.
...and you, a delicacy - were I so lucky.
Stranger: be you friend or food? The mark is Her measure: show us the brand of the Absolute.
A twice-played serenade to my ears, my tasty kibble. We have a bargain!
Attack.
Now speak or go, before my cravings conquer me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Should suddenly sound all ogre-ish and stupid. He's talking to his stupid brothers.

Text.Value: I am by all accounts a student of higher commerce and extortion.
Mm. Temptation knocks.
Dinnertime!
I notice you don't bear a brand of your own.
You're rather well-spoken for one of your kind.
Forget the goblins - why not work for me instead?
I've no use for the Absolute - or any god. I follow two masters only: gluttony and greed.
Do not test the Absolute's finest, ogre. You would not survive Her wrath.

EditorData.logicalname: Available if failed the first roll

Text.Value: I'm not your friend, and I'm not food. Back off.
I will keep close. When you are ready, sound the horn.
A slip of the tongue - you meant to make a better offer, surely.
I'll give you [463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca] gold - after you fight for me.
Am I not astonishing? A robust diet makes for a shrewd mind, you see. I am a gourmand...
I'll pay you in the flesh of the fallen - you'll have your fill.
Indeed? How regrettable, that your meat must go unsavoured.
Unh. You wound me, creature. I can hardly resist you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Absolutely stricken by this creature he would LOVE to eat

Text.Value: I'll give you [463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca] gold - after you fight for me.
Even sweeter still.
I expect more than your word. Show me your flesh.
I'll leave that to your imagination.
Mm, mm, mm. Fortune favours my belly, for there is no meat more succulent than a stranger's.
Tell me, sweet creature: does your flesh taste as honeyed as I could hope for?
Leave.
And this land proves particularly... fruitful.
...and the rest sate my hunger for meat.
I bear no such brand.
Show him your brand.
Spoken with the confidence only a True Soul could muster!
The goblins understand my appetites. They sate my hunger for gold...
Oh, but you do love to tease.
How regrettable. Tell me, sweet creature: does your flesh taste as honeyed as I could hope for?
Make an offer. Tempt me.
Mm - your candour makes you all the more enticing.
Alas - not so much as a nibble.
I'll pay you in the flesh of the fallen - you'll have your fill.
Use it when the need arises - and never a moment before.
Take my bonehorn. One blow, and... just a moment. It's been thieved - and I know the culprit.
I see it. How regrettable, that your meat must go unsavoured.
Would you like to work for me?
How regrettable, that your meat must go unsavoured.
I've changed my mind. Forget about it.
Come, now. An ogre feasts not on promises.
Leave.
I follow the scents of blood and gold to all lands fertile, friend.
I simply look for marks. Gold is more than sufficient compensation.
Take my bonehorn. One blow, and the ground will quake with my family name.
A brilliant notion, and a boon to my aching belly. We have a deal, my tasty kibble!
I'll give you [6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54] gold if I can call you into battle.
A serenade to my ears, and a boon to my belly. We've a bargain, my tasty kibble!
Yes, yes - the mark is unmistakable. Tell me, sweet creature: does your flesh taste as honeyed as I could hope for?
Ha! Did you expect The Enlightened to fall for such a crude ruse?
Flash your arm at him. There you are. You could see the brand, could you not?

Text.Value: How regrettable. Tell me, sweet creature: does your flesh taste as honeyed as I could hope for?
You speak with an eloquence unusual for your kind.
You're quite eloquent for an ogre.
I know of your kind, but you're among the first I've seen.
I've seen few other ogres in these parts.
...and you, a delicacy - unless you bear the mark, of course.
Yes, yes - the mark is unmistakable. How regrettable, that your meat must go unsavoured.
Leave.
I'll do you one better - I'm one of her chosen disciples.

Synopsis: Loomp is the smart ogre. he checks for your mark since he is working for the goblin boss. You can convince him (and his fellow ogres, if they are there) to join you in battle. He should sound intelligent and HUNGRY.
